2025/12/06 19:16:11 INFO dspy.teleprompt.mipro_optimizer_v2: 2: As a botanist in a critical situation, you have just discovered a single iris flower in the wild but do not have a microscope with you. You measure its petal and sepal dimensions using your gauge and get the following: Petal Length: 4.6 cm, Petal Width: 1.5 cm, Sepal Length: 6.1 cm, and Sepal Width: 2.8 cm. Given the petal and sepal dimensions, quickly predict the iris species to help decide the immediate next steps for further investigation!

